    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@dov - well you'd already need to handle the case where you get multiple values for mode, right?\n\n``` python\nIn [3]: pd.Series([2, 1, 2, 3, 3, 5]).mode()\nOut[3]:\n0    2\n1    3\ndtype: int64\n```\n\nI would suggest using `value_counts` instead - you can always do `series.value_counts().idxmax()`, which will always choose the earlier element when breaking ties:\n\n``` python\nIn [4]: pd.Series([2, 1, 2, 3, 3, 5]).value_counts().idxmax()\nOut[4]: 3\n\nIn [5]: pd.Series([6, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5]).value_counts().idxmax()\nOut[5]: 6\n```\n\nUltimately it's just being explicit about the data, because my guess is that you want to end up with dimensionality reduction with mode?\n"
  },
